<!-- 06 RECENT REPAIRS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">06, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">BlueStar jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Three representative service calls — model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; technical scenarios are typical of what we see on BlueStar service.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>BlueStar RNB366BV2 36-inch range, Beverly Hills</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Continuous clicking from the simmer burner even after the burner had lit. Owner reported it had been intermittent for a week before becoming constant. Other burners igniting normally. Unit was 5 years old, in the 2020 production cohort.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Classic 2016-2021 RNB simmer burner spark module failure pattern. Module stuck in continuous-spark mode. Other burner zones' modules tested clean. Ceramic igniters across all zones checked and within service spec — coastal-LA wear hadn't compounded the issue.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Spark module replacement with OEM Prizer-Painter part (in stock on truck for RNB series). Verified normal ignition and clean cycle on all five burners. Continuous-spark fault cleared.</p>
